properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 4 at 1:38AM MST until January 4 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High winds returning to portions of central Wyoming today...

.An approaching cold front will bring strong winds to portions of
western and central Wyoming late tonight and Saturday.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts 60 to 70 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range and Natrona
County Lower Elevations.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 8 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile
vehicles. Watch for strong cross winds on area roads, including
Interstate 25, US Highway 20 26 and along Wyoming Boulevard
south of Casper.
properties.instruction:
Use caution of travelling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust. In a parking lot,
park into the wind to minimize the possibility of your car door
hitting another parked vehicle.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 8 PM MST THIS EVENING
